         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. &amp; zool Garden ¶ 17. Nov. 59 ¶ My dear Professor Gray. ¶  ¶ I was equally delighted with your kind letter ¶  and your valuable contribution of plants &amp; seeds pr. "Huntress" &amp; am especial...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">59.11.17</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Asa Gray</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Gray Herbarium Archives, Harvard University, Cambridge, Massachusetts.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. &amp; zool Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17. Nov. 59</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Professor Gray.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was equally delighted with your kind letter<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> and your valuable contribution of plants &amp; seeds pr. "Huntress" &amp; am especially indebted to you for the singular <name key="Niviusia">Niviusia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Neviusia</seg>?</p>
               </note> The numerous publication, all of depth &amp; clearness, testify to the great assiduity and profound knowledge, which you display, and I congratulate myself that you condescended to enter with me in a so frequent intercourse of exchange &amp; correspondence. I hope to be able to make up at the end of the season (Febr. or March) a large collection of dried specimens &amp; seeds. Meanwhile also the first vol. (containing <name key="Thalamiflorae">Thalamiflorae</name>) of the "plants of Victoria"<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B62.03.03.</p>
               </note> &amp; also of the Fragmenta will be out,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B59.12.02.</p>
               </note> &amp; my report on the garden<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B60.01.01.</p>
               </note> and also on Mr Stuart's plants<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B60.06.01.</p>
               </note> from the N.W. interior of South Australia. The phil. Institute begs to offer its most grateful acknowledgement to the academy for the liberal donation of your volumes<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">At an ordinary meeting of the Philosophical Institute of Victoria, 16 November 1859, the following contributions were laid upon the table: '"Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences," Vols. I. to IV. inclusive (dating from May, 1846, to May, 1848); also Parts I. and II. of Volume VI. (new series) of the Memoirs of the "American Academy of Arts and Sciences" — by the Academy'. See <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Transactions of the Philosophical Institute of Victoria</seg>
                     <seg style="">, vol. 4</seg> (1860), p. xxviii.</p>
               </note> so replete with important information, &amp; only regrets that our young society is not yet strong enough to offer an equivalent acceptable to the scientific men of your great state.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The official acknowledgement will come through Dr Macadam.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With my sincerest admiration &amp; regard I remain, my very</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">dear Professor,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your attached</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">There is great demand here for <name key="Podophyllum">Podophyllum</name> as a medicinal herb.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The root of this plant was a source of the alkaloid Berberin. See B72.13.02.</p>
               </note> Could you favor me with a few seeds?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Niviusia">Niviusia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Podophyllum">Podophyllum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Thalamiflorae">Thalamiflorae</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
